```julia
using Dates

function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    if isa(dt, Date)
        error("Cannot add hours to a date without a time component. Use DateTime type instead.")
    end
    return dt + Hour(bump)
end
```

This function uses the `Dates` standard library and checks if the input `dt` is a `Date` type. If it is, an error message is thrown indicating that you cannot add hours to a date without a time component. The default value for `bump` is set to 3 hours.
